                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.001 L 76/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-20T16:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 20—9:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>273. Your 148, June 16, 4 p.m. Diplomatic body meeting this morning unanimously
                    accepted form of reply which I had drafted merely acknowledging receipt of
                    notification new President of accession.</p>
                <p>Chang Tso-lin and Wu Pei-fu’s representatives have reached an agreement. In 24
                    hours 18th and 19th, 358 cars loaded with guns, equipment and horses belonging
                    to Chang’s army left Shanhaikwan and Chang’s troops in large numbers are passing
                    beyond wall on foot.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
